<h2>What Makes a Photo Look "Scanned"?</h2>

<p>A real scanner produces a document that has three key characteristics:</p>

<ul>
  <li><strong>Grayscale</strong> — no colour noise or warm-light cast from lamps</li>
  <li><strong>White background</strong> — the paper appears clean white, not grey or cream</li>
  <li><strong>High-contrast text</strong> — letters are dark black with crisp, sharp edges</li>
</ul>

<p>
  A phone photo lacks all three: it's colour, the background is uneven, and the text can look soft
  because of focus or motion blur. The Photo to Scan Converter fixes all three using pixel-level adjustments.
</p>

